:mass_of_biological_material rdfs:subClassOf :mass_of_compounded_environmental_materials .
text: mass of biological material is a type of mass of compounded environmental materials.

A composting toilet is a type of dry toilet fixture. It is defined as a dry toilet fixture in which managed, aerobic decomposition converts human excreta into organic matter suitable for the fertilization or amendment of soils.

Paraffin oil, also broadly known as paraffin and exactly referred to as liquid paraffin, is a type of fuel oil. It is characterized by being composed primarily of alkanes, specifically those having between 5-15 carbon atoms with the general formula CnH2n+2. Moreover, paraffin oil includes substances that are at least partly composed of elements found at the intersection of naphthalene and alkane. It is generally odorless or has only a slight odor, produces only small amounts of soot compared to other fuel oils, and is highly refined.

Natural gas is a type of hydrocarbon gas that serves as a fossil fuel, primarily composed of methane. It is defined as a hydrocarbon gas mixture that consists primarily of methane, but it commonly includes varying amounts of other higher alkanes, and sometimes a usually lesser percentage of carbon dioxide, nitrogen, and/or hydrogen sulfide. Natural gas is formed when layers of buried plants and gases are exposed to intense heat and pressure over thousands of years.

Liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) is a type of liquefied hydrocarbon gas with a definition that encompasses liquified petroleum gas or liquid petroleum gas, also referred to as simply propane or butane. These are flammable mixtures of hydrocarbon gases used as fuel in heating appliances, cooking equipment, and vehicles. It has exact synonyms including LP gas, LPG, and liquid petroleum gas. Additionally, it has a related synonym, liquified natural gas.

Hydrocarbon gas is defined as a gas that is primarily composed of hydrocarbon molecules. It is identified as the same as something that is both a gaseous environmental material and has at least some quality of a gas, and at the same time, it is also composed primarily of some hydrocarbon. Furthermore, hydrocarbon gas is classified as a type of gaseous environmental material as well as a type of hydrocarbon-based environmental material.
Compressed natural gas is a type of natural gas and something that has at least some increased pressure quality. It is defined as a natural gas stored at high pressures, typically 20–25 Megapascals.

Biogas is a type of hydrocarbon gas and is defined as a mixture of different gases produced by the breakdown of organic matter in the absence of oxygen. It is primarily composed of methane and carbon dioxide, and may contain small amounts of hydrogen sulfide, water, and siloxanes. Furthermore, biogas includes at least some part methane and carbon dioxide, underscoring its composition primarily of these components.

Liquefied natural gas (LNG), a type of liquefied hydrocarbon gas, is natural gas (predominantly methane, CH4) that has been converted to liquid form for ease of storage or transport. It occupies about 1/600th the volume of natural gas in the gaseous state and is characterized by being odorless, colorless, non-toxic, and non-corrosive. LNG achieves a higher reduction in volume compared to compressed natural gas (CNG), making its (volumetric) energy density 2.4 times greater than that of CNG or 60 percent of that of diesel fuel. Additionally, LNG is also known by its exact synonyms, "LNG" and "liquified natural gas."

Liquefied hydrocarbon gas is a type of environmental material that is both liquid and hydrocarbon-based. Additionally, it possesses qualities of being somewhat condensed and having some increased pressure.
Compressed biogas is a type of biogas and something that has an increased pressure quality. It is defined as biogas stored at increased pressures.

Charcoal is a type of organic, solid, and hydrocarbon-based environmental material that is at least an output of some pyrolysis. It is defined as a light, black residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by removing water and other volatile constituents from animal and vegetation substances. Charcoal is usually produced by slow pyrolysis, which involves the heating of wood or other substances in the absence of oxygen.
A paraffin lamp, which has the exact synonym "kerosene lamp," is a type of lamp. It is defined as a lighting device that burns paraffin to generate light and heat.

A flat wick lamp is a type of paraffin lamp defined as a simple paraffin lamp, which operates by burning paraffin drawn up through a wick via capillary action. It is also exactly synonymous with flat wick lamp.

A central draught lamp, which is a type of paraffin lamp, is defined as a paraffin lamp that burns a paraffin-saturated, tubular wick contained between two structural tubes and supplied with oxygen by a central draught of air through the innermost of these tubes. This lamp is also known exactly as an Argand lamp and a tubular round wick lamp, in addition to being referred to by its own name, central draught lamp.

A mantle lamp is a type of central draught lamp, which is defined as a central-draught lamp that includes a pear-shaped, fabric mesh containing thorium or other rare-earth salts placed over the burner. Upon first use, the fabric burns away, and the rare-earth salts are converted to oxides, leaving behind a very fragile structure. This structure incandesces, meaning it glows brightly when exposed to the heat of the burner flame.

A lantern is identified as a type of manufactured product and it is also considered a type of object that includes, at least in part, a lamp. Furthermore, a lantern is defined as a portable device or mounted fixture that consists of a light source encased in a translucent cover.
A lamp is a type of manufactured product with the definition that it is an object which generates heat, light, or any other form of radiation.

A paraffin lantern is a type of lantern that includes a paraffin lamp as part of its structure. It is defined as a lantern that houses a paraffin lamp within a framework made of soldered or crimped-together sheet metal stampings and glass or other translucent materials. Additionally, paraffin lanterns are exactly synonymous with barn lanterns, hurricane lanterns, and kerosene lanterns.
A tubular paraffin lantern is a type of paraffin lantern, defined as a paraffin lantern that includes metal tubes in its casing, which direct air to the burning wick.

A dead flame paraffin lantern, which is a type of paraffin lantern, is defined as a paraffin lantern with a wick housed in a glass globe. This configuration allows airflow to be channeled upwards by vents located below the burning wick, coupled with an open chimney above it. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with the term "glass globe lantern."

The hot blast paraffin lantern, which is a type of tubular paraffin lantern, is defined as a device that collects hot air from the top of the lantern globe and circulates it through metal tubes to the burning wick.

A cold blast paraffin lantern is a type of tubular paraffin lantern defined as a tubular paraffin lantern that collects cool air from around the top of the lantern globe and circulates it, through metal tubes, to the burning wick.
An electric lamp is a type of lamp which is defined as a lamp that produces light from electricity.

A battery-powered electric lamp is a type of electric lamp, defined as an electric lamp that draws its power from a device composed of two or more electrochemical cells that convert stored chemical energy into electrical energy.

A candle is a type of lamp and also a type of object that is at least composed primarily of some wax. Additionally, a candle is defined as a lamp composed of wax within which an ignitable wick is embedded.

Wax is a type of environmental material defined as an environmental material primarily composed of lipids or other organic compounds consisting of long alkyl chains. Waxes are malleable near ambient temperatures and melt at approximately 45 degrees Celsius.
An apiary, which is a type of agricultural ecosystem, is defined as a place where beehives of honey bees are kept and maintained by beekeepers.

A radio device is a type of manufactured product that is defined as a device capable of receiving and/or transmitting information encoded in electromagnetic radiation through wave modulation. It is broadly synonymous with the term radio and has more specific narrow synonyms, including radio receiver and radio transmitter.
A cassette player, also known as a cassette deck or cassette recorder, is a type of manufactured product. It is defined as a device capable of playing and recording audio compact cassettes.

A television set, broadly synonymous with television and exactly synonymous with TV, telly, and tube, is categorized as a type of manufactured product. It is defined as a device that combines a tuner, display, and loudspeakers with the purpose of converting digital or analog information signals into moving images and sound.

A telephone, which is a type of manufactured product, is defined as a telecommunications device that converts sound into electronic signals suitable for transmission via cables or other transmission media, and reconverts such signals back into sound waves. Additionally, the telephone is exactly synonymous with the term "phone."

A mobile phone, which is a type of telephone, has the definition: A mobile phone is a telephone that transmits sound information to a mobile phone network via radio transmissions. It is exactly synonymous with cell phone, cellular phone, and hand phone.
A landline telephone is a type of telephone that is defined as a device connected to a telephone network via wires through which electronic signals are carried.

A refrigerator is defined as a device that consists of a thermally insulated compartment and a mechanical, chemical, or electronic heat pump. This pump transfers heat from the inside of the fridge to its external environment, ensuring that the inside of the fridge is cooled to a temperature below the ambient temperature of the room. It is a type of manufactured product that encompasses at least a part located with some refrigerant. Additionally, a refrigerator has the exact synonym "fridge."
A table is a type of piece of furniture, defined as a form of furniture with a flat horizontal upper surface used to support objects, for storage, show, and/or manipulation.
A desk is a type of table and it is defined as a table which is intended for information-manipulation tasks, including writing and use of interactive electronics.
A chair is a type of piece of furniture with a raised surface commonly used to seat a single person, defined as such.

A piece of furniture is a type of manufactured product, which is defined as a movable object intended to support various human activities such as seating (e.g., chairs, stools, and sofas) and sleeping (e.g., beds).

A sofa, which is a type of bench, is defined as a bench that is partially or entirely upholstered, and often fitted with springs and tailored cushions. Additionally, a sofa has exact synonyms including "couch" and "settee."
A bench is a type of piece of furniture, defined as a piece of furniture on which several people may sit at the same time.
A mattress is a type of piece of furniture defined as a mass of material that can cushion and support a reclining body, used as or on a bed.

A bed frame is a type of piece of furniture, which is defined as a piece of furniture used to position a mattress and bed base and may include a means of supporting a canopy. Additionally, bed frame has a related synonym, bedstead.
A bed base, also known as a bed foundation, is a type of piece of furniture that supports a mattress.

A framed bed is a type of piece of furniture, specifically one that at least includes parts such as a mattress, a bed frame, and a bed base. It is defined as a piece of furniture composed of a mattress supported by a bed base and held in place by a bed frame.
A cabinet is a type of piece of furniture which is defined as a roughly cuboidal piece used to store miscellaneous items in compartments accessible through doors or drawers.

A cupboard is a type of cabinet and it also has a synonym, closet. It is defined as a cabinet used indoors to store household objects such as food, crockery, textiles, and liquor, protecting them from dust and dirt.
A clock is a type of manufactured product, which is an instrument that may indicate, keep, and/or co-ordinate time. Additionally, it has a related synonym, "timepiece."

A pressure lamp is a type of lamp with a specific definition. A pressure lamp is a portable paraffin or oil lamp in which fuel is forced up into the mantle or burner by air pressure in the reservoir, which can be increased by pumping with a plunger.
A freshwater spring is a type of spring and is also a type of entity that is at least adjacent to some fresh water. It is defined as a spring through which fresh water flows.
River water is a type of liquid water and is considered to be part of, at least partially, some river.

Rainwater is a type of fresh water and is an output of some hydrological precipitation process. It is defined as liquid water that has precipitated in the form of droplets through the condensation of atmospheric water vapor.

A motor vehicle is defined as a vehicle that is propelled by an engine or motor and does not operate on rails. It is the same as something that intersects a vehicle and something that at least has part some motor. Furthermore, a motor vehicle is a type of vehicle and also a type of something that at least has part some motor.
A truck is a type of motor vehicle with a primary function of transporting cargo rather than human passengers. It is also exactly synonymous with the term lorry.
A water truck is a type of truck with the definition that it is a truck which transports water.
A vehicle falls under the category of manufactured products, and it is defined as a mobile machine that transports people or cargo.

A car is a type of motor vehicle with a definition stating that it is a wheeled motor vehicle used primarily for the transportation of human passengers. Most definitions specify that cars are designed to run primarily on roads, have seating for one to eight people, typically have four wheels, and are constructed principally for the transport of people rather than goods.
A cart is a type of vehicle, which is defined as a vehicle with two wheels designed to transport human passengers or cargo.
An animal-drawn cart is a type of cart with the definition that it is attached to one or more working or draught animals.
A boat is a type of watercraft, which is defined as a watercraft of any size that is able to float or plane on water.

A motor boat is a type of motor vehicle as well as a type of boat. It is defined as a boat which is propelled by a motor. Additionally, the terms "motorised boat" and "motorized boat" are exact synonyms for a motor boat.
A motor is a type of manufactured product, which is a machine designed to convert one or more forms of energy into mechanical energy. It also has an exact synonym, "engine."
A bus is a type of motor vehicle which is defined as a road vehicle designed to carry many passengers.

A taxicab, which is a type of car, has an exact synonym cab and another exact synonym taxi. It is defined as a car that may be hired, along with its operator, to transport passengers between locations of their choosing.
Watercraft is a type of vehicle, defined as a vehicle that is able to travel on or through water.

A bicycle is a type of vehicle that is human-powered, pedal-driven, and a single-track vehicle, having two wheels attached to a frame, one behind the other. It also has broad synonyms such as bike and cycle.
A motorcycle is a type of motor vehicle, which is defined as a two- or three-wheeled motor vehicle. It has broad synonyms such as bike and cycle, and exact synonyms like moto and motorbike.

A motorscooter is a type of motorcycle, which is also known as a scooter or motor scooter. It is defined as a motorcycle with a step-through frame and a platform for the rider's feet. Furthermore, "scooter" is considered a broad synonym for motorscooter, while "motor scooter" is an exact synonym.
A lentic water body is a type of water body defined as a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.
A lotic water body is a type of water body defined by its characteristic of accumulated water, in its totality, being in a state of flow.

A closed ecological system, which does not rely on matter exchange with any part outside the system, is a type of vivarium. This defines a closed ecological system as a vivarium that operates independently of external matter exchange.

A mesocosm is a type of vivarium, defined as a vivarium that is embedded within a natural environment. It is used to place a relatively small part of that environment under experimental control for the purposes of scientific investigation.

A microcosm is a type of vivarium and it is defined as a vivarium within which a simple ecosystem is artificially established and used to simulate and predict the behavior of natural ecosystems under controlled conditions.

Vaporisation is identified as a type of material transformation process, which necessitates at least an input that is both an environmental material and possesses the qualities of a liquid. Similarly, it requires an output that is also an environmental material but exhibits the qualities of a gas. Moreover, the definition of vaporisation is the process whereby an element or compound undergoes a phase transition from the liquid phase to vapor. Additionally, vaporisation is exactly synonymous with vaporization.

Boiling is a type of vaporization. It is defined as a form of vaporization which occurs when a liquid is heated to a temperature at which the vapor pressure of the liquid is equal to the pressure exerted on the liquid by the surrounding environmental pressure.

The hydrological condensation process is a type of condensation process, hydrological process, and something that at least has input some atmospheric water vapor and output some liquid water. It is defined as a process in which atmospheric water vapor undergoes a phase transition from the gas phase to the liquid phase. Additionally, the hydrological condensation process has a broad synonym: condensation.

A manufactured cage, which is a type of manufactured product, is defined as a manufactured structure made of interspaced structural elements such as metal or wooden bars or wires held together in a way that they may be used to confine, contain, or protect something. Additionally, the term "cage" serves as a broad synonym for a manufactured cage.
A drylot is a type of feedlot, defined as an enclosure of limited size, usually bare of vegetation, and used for fattening livestock.
A feedlot is a type of agricultural ecosystem, defined as a plot of land on which livestock are fattened for market.

Plant litter is a type of caro 0000000, organic material, and something that at least has part some leaf and has the quality of being at least partially dead. It is defined as dead plant material, such as leaves, bark, needles, and twigs, that has fallen to the ground. Additionally, plant litter is exactly synonymous with duff, leaf litter, litterfall, soil litter, and tree litter.

Climate change is characterized as a type of environmental system process that necessitates input from some climate system. Furthermore, it is described as having an output that is an intersection of a climate system and fluctuations, indicating that climate change involves fluctuations within the climate system. The definition of climate change encompasses the long-term fluctuations in temperature, precipitation, wind, and all other aspects of the Earth's climate. It is influenced by external processes, such as variations in solar irradiance, the Earth's orbital parameters (including eccentricity, precession, and inclination), lithosphere motions, and volcanic activity, which contribute to climatic variation. Additionally, internal variations within the climate system, for example, changes in the abundance of greenhouse gases, might produce fluctuations of sufficient magnitude and variability to explain observed climate change through the feedback processes interconnecting the components of the climate system.

Acidification of an aquatic environment is identified as a type of environmental system process, which is defined as a process whereby the pH of an aquatic environment, biome, or water body is lowered. This process necessitates inputs from either a water body, aquatic biome, or aquatic environment. Furthermore, the outputs of this process encompass entities that are either part of a water body, an aquatic biome, or an aquatic environment, and specifically include entities that are a combination of liquid water with an increased acidity attribute.

Ocean acidification is a type of acidification that affects aquatic environments, specifically the ocean and sea. It involves a process where the pH of a sea or ocean is lowered, which is a result of increased acidity in the water. This process is characterized by its impact on both the ocean and sea, and it is defined by its interaction with sea water that has a quality of increased acidity.

A chonolith is a type of rock intrusion characterized by its irregular shape and a demonstrable base, distinguishing it from other types of irregularly-shaped intrusions. This defines a chonolith as an igneous rock intrusion.

Ecosystem-wide aerobic respiration is defined as a process that encompasses all aerobic respiration processes instantiated in an ecosystem. It is categorized under various types, including a type of ecosystem-wide respiration, a hydrological process, and a process that necessarily involves some form of aerobic respiration. Furthermore, this respiration process is characterized by its inputs and outputs; specifically, it requires inputs that are intersections of substances such as dioxygen and substances that play the role of an electron acceptor, as well as carbohydrates that serve as nutrients. The outputs of this process include substances that are combinations of carbon dioxide and liquid water.

A volcanic eruption is a multifaceted process that is categorized under hydrological and material transport processes. It fundamentally involves volcanoes and the planetary crust as participants. The initiation of this process requires magma as an input. Throughout the course of a volcanic eruption, several outputs are produced, including hydrogen sulfide, carbon dioxide, carbon monoxide, hydrogen chloride, dihydrogen, sulfur dioxide, and water vapor. Essentially, a volcanic eruption is defined as a process during which lava, tephra (comprising ash, lapilli, volcanic bombs, and blocks), along with assorted gases, are expelled from a volcanic vent or fissure.

A planetary landmass is a type of planetary surface and also a type of landmass. Moreover, it is defined as a landmass which is part of a planet and is a type of something that is at least surrounded by something that is not an intersection of environmental material and anything that has at least some quality of a liquid. Additionally, planetary landmass is broadly synonymous with land and is relatedly synonymous with ground.

A liquid planetary surface is defined as the intersection between a liquid surface of an astronomical body and at least part of some planet. This type of surface is categorized both as a type of planetary surface and as a type of liquid surface of an astronomical body. Additionally, a liquid planetary surface is related to the concept where a liquid material of a planet comes into contact with the atmosphere or outer space, serving as a synonym for this phenomenon.

Outer space is a type of environmental material and has a broad synonym, space. It is defined as a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium, as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust, and cosmic rays that exist between celestial bodies.

A planetary crust is defined as the outermost solid shell of a rocky planet or natural satellite, which is chemically distinct from the underlying mantle. It is a type of planetary structural layer and also considered a type of entity that possesses some quality of a solid. Additionally, "planetary crust" has a broad synonym: "crust."
